{
  "texts": [
    "Fortunately, these instances are rare.",
    "To address the stochastic nature of the minority-sampled generation, we engage in multiple conversations with the LLM and consider the majority of consistent answers as the final grammar.",
    "This approach shares similarities with selfconsistency checks [45] in the domain of prompt engineering, but it does not occur in chain-of-thought prompting.Through these approaches, the fuzzer is able to effectively obtain accurate grammar from the LLM across various protocols.",
    "The model output shown in Figure 6 demonstrates a portion of the RTSP grammar derived from the LLM.",
    "In practice, the LLMs are occasionally not sensitive to the word \"all\" in this prompt, resulting in them generating only part of grammar types."
  ]
}